\begin_layout Standard
The dynamic between two quadrotors 
\begin_inset Formula $Q_{i},$
\end_inset

 
\begin_inset Formula $Q_{j}$
\end_inset

 can be defined in terms of relative variables as follows [rechability-based
 safety and Goal Satisfaction p.
 6].
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{align*}
p_{x,r} & =p_{x,i}-p_{x,j}\\
p_{y,r} & =p_{y,i}-p_{y,j}\\
v_{x,r} & =v_{x,i}-v_{x,j}\\
v_{y,r} & =v_{y,i}-v_{y,j}
\end{align*}

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Where 
\begin_inset Formula $Q_{i}$
\end_inset

 is the evader and 
\begin_inset Formula $Q_{j}$
\end_inset

 is the pursuer and is consider as the model disturbance.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
In this case, we have
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{align*}
\dot{p}_{x,r} & =v_{x,r}\\
\dot{p}_{y,r} & =v_{y,r}\\
\dot{v}_{x,r} & =u_{x,i}-u_{x,j}\\
\dot{v}_{y,r} & =u_{y,i}-u_{y,j}
\end{align*}

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Rechability-Based Controllers.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsection
Avoiding collisions
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
We define an unsafe configuration when it is within a minimum separation
 distance 
\begin_inset Formula $d$
\end_inset

 to a reference vehicle in both the 
\begin_inset Formula $x$
\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset Formula $y$
\end_inset

 directions.
 In such a way we define the target set as follows:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
\mathcal{L}_{S}=\left\{ x:\text{\left|p_{x,r}\right|, \left|p_{y,r}\right|}\leq d\right\} 
\]

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The zero sublevel set of the associated HJ PDE
\end_layout

